Out[48]:
<AxesSubplot:>
  • There is strong positive correlation between profit and sales means as the sales increases profit is also increases.
  • We also see that there is negative correlation between profit and discount means as the discount increases the profit will be decreases.

Conclusion:¶

  • In this data we observe that,
  • For variable Category there are three categories (technology, furniture, office supplies), Technology gets more profit as compare to the furniture and office supplies, and furniture has more discount as compare to the office supplies and technology. hence even if you give a big discount on furniture, yet its sales and profit will be less than technology and in other hand if you doesn’t give a more discount on technology, its sales and profit is high.
  • For Subcategory, there are 16 subcategories (appliances, art, binders, bookcases, chairs, copiers, envelopes, fasteners, furnishings, labels, machines, paper, phones, storage, supplies, tables), The quantity is the same for all the subcategories only the fasteners are little higher than the others, yet its sales and profit not much obtained, the discount on machines and tables are high so their sales are also good.
  • For variable Segment, there are three segments such as consumer, corporate and home office. All the three segments have same sales and almost same quantity. Segment home office have little bit more profit as compare to the others two. Hence if you give a big discount on consumer and corporate, yet its profit is little bit small as compare to home office.
  • For Region wise comparison, the quantity is almost same for all region. The central region is give more discount but the sales are higher in the west region and the profit is also higher in the west region.
  • For Order Year, the quantity is the same for every year. And the discount is also almost same for all years, but still as the years increase the sales seem to be decrease. And the profit is increased in 2017 as compare.
